      • getIdentifier

        @NotNull
public @NotNull String getIdentifier()
        Other known identifier used for the same taxon. Can be a URL pointing to a webpage, an xml or rdf document, a DOI, UUID or any other identifer.

        Example: urn:lsid:ipni.org:names:692570-1:1.4

        Returns:
        the identifier.

      • getIdentifierLink

        @Nullable
public String getIdentifierLink()
        Creates a http link for an identifier if possible by passing it to some known resolvers for the specific id type. If no link can be constructed, null is returned.
        Returns:
        the url or null if it cannot be created
        See Also:
        IdentifierUtils.getIdentifierLink(String, org.gbif.api.vocabulary.IdentifierType)
